        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 10:47PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 1047 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monticello, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monticello, Liberty, Fallsburg, Neversink, South Fallsburg,
Woodridge, Swan Lake, Harris, Loch Sheldrake, Hurleyville, Kiamesha,
Woodbourne, Mongaup Valley, Maplewood, Thompsonville, Grahamsville,
Rock Hill, Smallwood, Hasbrouck, and Glen Wild.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
